OQ-1 (tidal > 0.10g at r=3.25m in M8I):
  Root cause: Z'(r0)=0 when delta=0.5m => b'(r0)=0 => tidal peaks sharply near r0.
  Fix (M8I-Throat v1.2): wider delta=1.89m spreads Z gradient over r in [3, ~6.78m].
  Result: max tidal in bulk (r>3.25m) = 0.0999g < 0.10g.  OQ-1 CLOSED.

OQ-2 (transit 7.71ns vs supervisor's claimed 1.08ns in M8I):
  Root cause: supervisor's original b(r) table (1.08ns result) was internally
  inconsistent with the stated ODE (Z-field Einstein equation).
  Fix: supervisor recalibrates to delta=1.89m. Correct b(r) gives:
    L_proper = 7.36m -> Delta_tau = 7.71ns.
  This matches M8I's certified computation (7.3581m / 7.711ns).  OQ-2 CLOSED.

